# Trading Dashboard — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) at the repo root and fill in
# your own keys. Both filenames are gitignored. None of the keys below
# are required for the core dashboard (yfinance + Crypto.com REST need no
# auth) — they only unlock the optional features called out per-key.

# ── Anthropic — required for the screenshot-to-kill-sheet extractor ─────────
# Used by `src/vision/options_extractor.py` to parse broker-screenshot
# option chains into structured kill-sheet input. Without this set, the
# dashboard still works but you'll fill in option details manually.
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# ── FRED — optional, used by Tier 4 regime-health macro signals ─────────────
# Pulls macro series (VIX term structure, HY OAS, etc.) from the St. Louis
# Fed FRED API. Without this, Tier 4 regime widgets render as N/A but
# everything else (Tier 1/2/3) works normally.
# Free key at https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
FRED_API_KEY=

# ── Polygon — optional alternative price provider ───────────────────────────
# `src/data/polygon_loader.py` is wired but defaults to OFF — the dashboard
# uses yfinance for stocks/ETFs. Set this AND wire the loader if you'd
# rather pay for a stable feed than depend on yfinance's free tier.
# https://polygon.io/dashboard/api-keys
POLYGON_API_KEY=
